race.description: Gold Sponsors Club Now Open Handicap (C1)
race.comment: CAPITAL DANCER (2) strong mare plagued by the wet tracks last preparation. Goes well fresh and her lone victory came over this trip. Returns with the one good trial and gets the right setup from the gate. Hard to stop. DER BLAUE REITER (7) registered his first win on resumption with a slick on-pace victory over 900m at Albury on December 13. Since scored a 900m trial win at Canberra. Serious contender again with the high confidence. BRUMMAGEN (5) placed at this track and trip and is worth another chance with Stiff's 3kg claim. Complete mystery after he failed to close off when ninth over 1000m at Dubbo. Assess on his good earlier efforts. ZOUKING (4) returned from a lengthy break with a dominant on-pace win over 1000m at Kempsey with the 59kg. Has the figures to tackle this tougher contest.
